      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "FILE CONVERSION"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Introduction: File conversion allows files to be copied from one"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "file format to another, as determined by the SOURCE and"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "DESTINATION profile types.  During file conversion, a file is"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "read in based upon its SOURCE PROFILE characteristics, and is"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "written out based upon its DESTINATION PROFILE characteristics."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "The fields use to specify the specifics of a file conversion"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "are as follows:"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "SOURCE FILE"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "NAME+-Specifies the file that is to be converted to another"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "file format.  Unless the entire pathname of the file is specified,"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "the file is assumed to be in the directory as specified by the"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "CURRENT DIR field above."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "field_row",
        "fields": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "(Press"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "ENTER+for next page)"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
